  "texts": [
    "Then, in rainbow-ladder (RL) truncation [40,41], the five-point Schwinger function that defines the π + ( p) → π + ( p) elastic electromagnetic form factor takes the form drawn in the top diagram of Fig. 1.",
    "This image translates into where 2Pγ π ν (P, Q) = 2N c tr D d 4 l (2π) 4 γ ν (l+ p, l+ p)L(l, P, Q), (1a) L(l, P, Q) = S(l + p) π (l + p/2; p)S(l) × ¯ π (l + p /2; -p)S(l + p),(1b)= p + p, Q = p -p, p • p = -m 2 π = p• p, with m π being the pion mass, P • Q = 0.",
    "Further, S(k) = 1/[iγ • k A(k 2) + B(k 2)]is the dressed-quark propagator, calculated in rainbow truncation; π is the RL-truncation pion Bethe-Salpeter amplitude; and γ ν is the RL dressed photon+quark vertex.",
    "(For an overview, see, e.g., Refs.",
    "Since the gluons that bind the π do not carry electric charge, then, in RL truncation, insofar as γ π ν is concerned, the bottom diagram in Fig. 1 is zero.Regarding Eq."
  ]
